         <abstract id="aspace_5c851fb7377b4c5eb6a784bffacd93b7">Correspondence, journal, speeches and miscellanea of William F. Shunk and his family. Shunk exchanged letters with family members in Pennsylvania while sailing around the world, circa 1846-1849. The sloop, <title render="italic">
               <part>Preble</part>
            </title>, stopped in many ports, including Cape Verdes, Rio de Janiero, Hawaii, Hong Kong, and Canton, China. Speeches of his father, Francis Rawn Shunk, governor of Pennsylvania, are also included.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2007058291"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Shunk, William Findlay, 1830-1907</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
